				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I would argue wheather you need to do WToV before NToV.
<br />

<br />
My guild is one of the oldest on Xev and quite a lot of the people in the uber guilds have had some association to PTA. Only recently have my guild gained a size and average level that has allowed us to have some of the higher zones on our dance card.
<br />

<br />
We have done HoT, but we also found that except for one or two of the quest drops for most classes, what we already had from trade skills, quests and the bazaar were as good or better.
<br />

<br />
We did talk about starting WToV and had one attempt at LtK (which failed, because we hd too few people on, they were the wrong classes and we were unlucky)
<br />

<br />
Then one saturday we found Sontalak up and desided to give him a try. And we were succesfull
<br />
<a href="http://www.povartarewalliance.org/announcements/index.shtml?action=show&start=6" target="_blank">http://www.povartarewalliance.org/announcements/index.shtml?action=show&start=6</a>
<br />
even with Esorpa of the ring as an add!!
<br />

<br />
Then we find that Aaryonar is up and kill him succesfully, which due to the server agreement gives us three days to clear out NToV. We log on the next day and clears NToV in about 8 hours without any big problems except a little accident with the triplets.
<br />

<br />
The point of this is if you are reasonable geared by todays standards, you don't have to go from west to north and NToV gear is even by todays standard something to drool over.
<br />

<br />
nmee<br />_________________<br /><A href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=407265">Nmee Lightarch</A>
<br />
Prestidigitator
<br />
<A href="http://www.povartarewalliance.org/">Povar Tarew Alliance</A></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
